<subSubSection pageId="1" pageNumber="231" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,916,1807]" pageId="1" pageNumber="231">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,334,988,1014]" pageId="1" pageNumber="231">Etymology.</emphasis>
The species is named for Howard Everest Hinton (1912–1977) one of the coleopterists of the twentieth century, who was born and raised in 
<collectingCountry box="[695,783,1024,1050]" name="Mexico" pageId="1" pageNumber="231">Mexico</collectingCountry>
, and collected the unique 
<typeStatus box="[1089,1191,1024,1050]" pageId="1" pageNumber="231">holotype</typeStatus>
. In a coincidence, he started his university education at the same institution as one of us (MAI), Modesto Junior College in Modesto, California.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="1" pageNumber="231" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,916,1807]" pageId="1" pageNumber="231">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,322,1132,1158]" pageId="1" pageNumber="231">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authorityName="Ferreira &amp; Keller &amp; Ivie" authorityYear="2022" box="[332,539,1132,1158]" class="Insecta" family="Lampyridae" genus="Chespirito" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="231" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hintoni">
<emphasis box="[332,539,1132,1158]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="231">Chespirito hintoni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
can be separated from other 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Ferreira, Keller and Branham" authorityYear="2020" box="[885,1003,1132,1158]" class="Insecta" family="Lampyridae" genus="Chespirito" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="231" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[885,1003,1132,1158]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="231">Chespirito</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the combination of a unicolorous brownish pronotum and elytra (
<figureCitation box="[496,581,1168,1194]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[180,1407,181,1919]" captionTargetId="figure-20@3.[180,1407,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 1. Dorsal habitus of Chespirito species.A) C. hintoni. B) C. costae. C). C. milleri. Ventral view of last three abdominal tergites (6–8). D) C. hintoni. E) C. costae. F). C. milleri. Dorsal view of last three abdominal ventrites. G) C. hintoni. H) C. costae. I). C. milleri. Scale bars: 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6405134" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6405134/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="231">Fig. 1A</figureCitation>
) (vs. the yellow pronotal disc in 
<taxonomicName box="[936,1099,1168,1195]" class="Insecta" family="Lampyridae" genus="Chespirito" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="231" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ballantynae">
<emphasis box="[936,955,1168,1194]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="231">C</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[967,1099,1168,1194]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="231">ballantynae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), the pronotum not constricted medially (
<figureCitation box="[265,352,1204,1230]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[180,1407,181,1919]" captionTargetId="figure-20@3.[180,1407,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 1. Dorsal habitus of Chespirito species.A) C. hintoni. B) C. costae. C). C. milleri. Ventral view of last three abdominal tergites (6–8). D) C. hintoni. E) C. costae. F). C. milleri. Dorsal view of last three abdominal ventrites. G) C. hintoni. H) C. costae. I). C. milleri. Scale bars: 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6405134" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6405134/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="231">Fig. 1A</figureCitation>
) (vs. constricted in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Ferreira, Keller &amp; Branham" authorityYear="2020" box="[579,722,1204,1231]" class="Insecta" family="Lampyridae" genus="Chespirito" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="231" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="zaragozai">
<emphasis box="[579,598,1204,1230]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="231">C</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[612,722,1205,1230]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="231">zaragozai</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), the last three abdominal segments distinctly yellow (
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[180,1407,181,1919]" captionTargetId="figure-20@3.[180,1407,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 1. Dorsal habitus of Chespirito species.A) C. hintoni. B) C. costae. C). C. milleri. Ventral view of last three abdominal tergites (6–8). D) C. hintoni. E) C. costae. F). C. milleri. Dorsal view of last three abdominal ventrites. G) C. hintoni. H) C. costae. I). C. milleri. Scale bars: 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6405134" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6405134/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="231">Fig. 1D, 1G</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[202,238,1240,1266]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1924,1948]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,181,1901]" captionTargetId="figure-18@4.[151,1435,181,1901]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 2. Lateral habitus of Chespirito species. A) C. hintoni. B) C. costae. C). C. milleri. Apically notched and bifurcated ventrite 7 in detail. D–E) C. milleri. Scale bars: A–C = 1 mm, D–E = 100 µm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6405136" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6405136/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="231">2A</figureCitation>
) (vs. dark brown in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Ferreira, Keller &amp; Branham" authorityYear="2020" box="[476,575,1240,1267]" class="Insecta" family="Lampyridae" genus="Chespirito" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="231" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lloydi">
<emphasis box="[476,495,1240,1266]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="231">C</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[511,575,1240,1266]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="231">lloydi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
or not distinctly yellow in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Ferreira, Keller &amp; Branham" authorityYear="2020" box="[893,1038,1240,1267]" class="Insecta" family="Lampyridae" genus="Chespirito" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="231" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="zaragozai">
<emphasis box="[893,912,1240,1266]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="231">C</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[928,1038,1241,1266]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="231">zaragozai</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) and by having ventrite 8 notched medially (
<figureCitation box="[264,349,1276,1302]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[180,1407,181,1919]" captionTargetId="figure-20@3.[180,1407,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 1. Dorsal habitus of Chespirito species.A) C. hintoni. B) C. costae. C). C. milleri. Ventral view of last three abdominal tergites (6–8). D) C. hintoni. E) C. costae. F). C. milleri. Dorsal view of last three abdominal ventrites. G) C. hintoni. H) C. costae. I). C. milleri. Scale bars: 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6405134" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6405134/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="231">Fig. 1D</figureCitation>
) (vs. entire in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Ferreira, Keller &amp; Branham" authorityYear="2020" box="[510,608,1276,1303]" class="Insecta" family="Lampyridae" genus="Chespirito" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="231" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lloydi">
<emphasis box="[510,529,1276,1302]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="231">C</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[542,608,1276,1302]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="231">lloydi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis box="[609,726,1276,1302]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="231">
, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Ferreira &amp; Keller &amp; Ivie" authorityYear="2022" box="[619,726,1276,1302]" class="Insecta" family="Lampyridae" genus="Chespirito" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="231" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="milleri">C. milleri</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Ferreira &amp; Keller &amp; Ivie" authorityYear="2022" box="[779,883,1276,1303]" class="Insecta" family="Lampyridae" genus="Chespirito" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="231" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="costae">
<emphasis box="[779,798,1276,1302]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="231">C</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[811,883,1277,1302]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="231">costae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) and tergite 8 entire, round apically (
<figureCitation box="[1294,1379,1276,1302]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[180,1407,181,1919]" captionTargetId="figure-20@3.[180,1407,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 1. Dorsal habitus of Chespirito species.A) C. hintoni. B) C. costae. C). C. milleri. Ventral view of last three abdominal tergites (6–8). D) C. hintoni. E) C. costae. F). C. milleri. Dorsal view of last three abdominal ventrites. G) C. hintoni. H) C. costae. I). C. milleri. Scale bars: 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6405134" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6405134/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="231">Fig. 1G</figureCitation>
) (vs. tergite VIII notched apically in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Ferreira &amp; Keller &amp; Ivie" authorityYear="2022" box="[504,612,1312,1338]" class="Insecta" family="Lampyridae" genus="Chespirito" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="231" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="milleri">
<emphasis box="[504,612,1312,1338]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="231">C. milleri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="1" pageNumber="231" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,916,1807]" pageId="1" pageNumber="231">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,345,1348,1374]" pageId="1" pageNumber="231">Description.</emphasis>
General color dark brown (
<figureCitation box="[654,754,1348,1374]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[180,1407,181,1919]" captionTargetId="figure-20@3.[180,1407,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 1. Dorsal habitus of Chespirito species.A) C. hintoni. B) C. costae. C). C. milleri. Ventral view of last three abdominal tergites (6–8). D) C. hintoni. E) C. costae. F). C. milleri. Dorsal view of last three abdominal ventrites. G) C. hintoni. H) C. costae. I). C. milleri. Scale bars: 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6405134" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6405134/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="231">Figs. 1A</figureCitation>
); mandibles and last three abdominal segments yellow (
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[180,1407,181,1919]" captionTargetId="figure-20@3.[180,1407,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 1. Dorsal habitus of Chespirito species.A) C. hintoni. B) C. costae. C). C. milleri. Ventral view of last three abdominal tergites (6–8). D) C. hintoni. E) C. costae. F). C. milleri. Dorsal view of last three abdominal ventrites. G) C. hintoni. H) C. costae. I). C. milleri. Scale bars: 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6405134" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6405134/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="231">Figs. 1D</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[200,238,1384,1410]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1924,1948]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,181,1901]" captionTargetId="figure-18@4.[151,1435,181,1901]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 2. Lateral habitus of Chespirito species. A) C. hintoni. B) C. costae. C). C. milleri. Apically notched and bifurcated ventrite 7 in detail. D–E) C. milleri. Scale bars: A–C = 1 mm, D–E = 100 µm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6405136" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6405136/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="231">2A</figureCitation>
