<figureCitation box="[704,795,1420,1446]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[180,1407,181,1919]" captionTargetId="figure-20@3.[180,1407,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 1. Dorsal habitus of Chespirito species.A) C. hintoni. B) C. costae. C). C. milleri. Ventral view of last three abdominal tergites (6–8). D) C. hintoni. E) C. costae. F). C. milleri. Dorsal view of last three abdominal ventrites. G) C. hintoni. H) C. costae. I). C. milleri. Scale bars: 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6405134" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6405134/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="231">Fig. 1A</figureCitation>
). Antenna short and stubby, when extending posteriorly barely surpassing humeral region (
<figureCitation box="[549,640,1456,1482]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[180,1407,181,1919]" captionTargetId="figure-20@3.[180,1407,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 1. Dorsal habitus of Chespirito species.A) C. hintoni. B) C. costae. C). C. milleri. Ventral view of last three abdominal tergites (6–8). D) C. hintoni. E) C. costae. F). C. milleri. Dorsal view of last three abdominal ventrites. G) C. hintoni. H) C. costae. I). C. milleri. Scale bars: 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6405134" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6405134/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="231">Fig. 1A</figureCitation>
). Pronotum not constricted medially; anterior angles round; posterior margin bisinuate (
<figureCitation box="[358,450,1492,1518]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[180,1407,181,1919]" captionTargetId="figure-20@3.[180,1407,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 1. Dorsal habitus of Chespirito species.A) C. hintoni. B) C. costae. C). C. milleri. Ventral view of last three abdominal tergites (6–8). D) C. hintoni. E) C. costae. F). C. milleri. Dorsal view of last three abdominal ventrites. G) C. hintoni. H) C. costae. I). C. milleri. Scale bars: 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6405134" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6405134/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="231">Fig. 1A</figureCitation>
); with median longitudinal carina strongly visible throughout (
<figureCitation box="[1173,1264,1492,1518]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[180,1407,181,1919]" captionTargetId="figure-20@3.[180,1407,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 1. Dorsal habitus of Chespirito species.A) C. hintoni. B) C. costae. C). C. milleri. Ventral view of last three abdominal tergites (6–8). D) C. hintoni. E) C. costae. F). C. milleri. Dorsal view of last three abdominal ventrites. G) C. hintoni. H) C. costae. I). C. milleri. Scale bars: 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6405134" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6405134/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="231">Fig. 1A</figureCitation>
